Dispute_Type: Unpaid hire and damages under a maritime charterparty agreement
Legal_Issue: Whether the plaintiff's claim can be resolved via summary judgment and whether the counterclaim should be referred to arbitration
Procedural_Stage: Motion for summary judgment and arbitration referral
Evidence_Assessment: Genuine disputes over charterparty interpretation, including deductions, agency fees, and vessel delays
Decision_Outcome: Summary judgment denied; counterclaim not referred to arbitration
Burden_of_Proof: Plaintiff failed to show absence of genuine issues of fact
Legal_Rule: Summary judgment requires no genuine issue of fact or law; arbitration must be timely invoked
Standard_of_Review: Rule 432.3 and 432.6 standard for summary judgment
Grounds_for_Claim: Unpaid hire and expenses under charterparty agreement
Review_Standard: No genuine issue of fact or law
Procedural_Fairness_Assessment: Both parties engaged in litigation, indicating waiver of arbitration
Key_Evidence_Considered: Charterparty terms, timing of arbitration request, conduct of parties
Legal_Framework: Federal Court Rules, Commercial Arbitration Act
Applicant_Challenge: Seeking summary judgment and arbitration referral
Court_Result: Motion denied, case proceeds to trial
Defendant_Response: Opposed motion, cited unresolved factual disputes
Remedy_Requested: Summary judgment on claim, referral of counterclaim to arbitration
Outcome: Both claims to proceed to trial
Remedy_Sought: Payment of unpaid hire and expenses, dismissal of counterclaim or its referral to arbitration
Grounds_for_Inadmissibility_or_Allegatio: Waiver of arbitration due to delay
Applicable_Process: Summary judgment process, arbitration referral under statute
